         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 25/4/74. ¶  ¶ The fossil just received from you, reverend &amp; venerable friend, belongs to my genus Phymatocaryon (among Sapindaceae). You will observe, that the fruit is valvular, which is ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.04.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Branwhite Clarke</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.3608 Clarke papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS envelope front: 'On Her Majesty's [Service] | Rev. W. B. Cl[arke] | M.A., F.Z.S., [...] | Northshore | Sydney', and '<seg style="text-transform: uppercase; ">Government Botanist</seg>
                     <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">,</seg> | Melbourne, 25. Apr 1874.' <seg style="">For a published version of this letter, see Moyal (2003), pp. 1029-30.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25/4/74.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The fossil just received from you, reverend &amp; venerable friend, belongs to my genus Phymatocaryon (among <name key="Sapindaceae">Sapindaceae</name>). You will observe, that the fruit is valvular, which is not the case in <name key="Santalum">Santalum</name> &amp; <name key="Fusanus">Fusanus</name>. The species indeed comes very near Ph. MacKayi, so far as I can judge without sacrificing by dissection the only specimen.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should think it likely that many specimens of this particular fruit will be found in the (tertiary?) drifts, to which after all probably the stratum belongs, in which it was imbedded.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <name key="Phymatocaryon%20MacKayi">Phymatocaryon MacKayi</name> is as yet but found on one spot, but there in considerable quantity and accompanied by fruits of other genera, all of which proving new and described by me in the successive quarterly reports of our mining Department.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B71.05.02; B71.08.01; B71.11.01; B73.11.01.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will gladly work any such fruits out, if several specimens of each can be sent, so that the necessary dissections can be effected.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your son, Major Clarke, I missed the day before yesterday,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mordaunt Clarke. See M to W. Clarke, 29 January 1874.</p>
               </note> when calling for the gallant Officer at Menzies Hotel. I hope to see him next week.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I gave to some of the scientific men on Board of the Challenger &amp; Arcona<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">The British oceanographical research vessel, HMS </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Challenger</seg>
                     <seg style="">, and the Prussian frigate </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Arcona</seg>
                     <seg style=""> were in Melbourne at the same time, and both left for Sydney at the beginning of April.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> letters to you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Trusting that you are well, I remain, rev. and dear friend, your ever regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Please convey my best salutation to Mrs Cobham.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mary Cobham.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Fusanus">Fusanus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Phymatocaryon%20MacKayi">Phymatocaryon MacKayi</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Santalum">Santalum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sapindaceae">Sapindaceae</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
